NHS West Yorkshire Integrated Care Board is inviting interested providers to apply to be part of a Dynamic Purchasing System (DPS) for the provision of Vasectomy Services for the population of Leeds.

To provide a community vasectomy service for patients registered with a GP Practice. The service will deliver an innovative, high quality, efficient service closer to patients' home.

The service will:
-Offer patients a choice of locations and appointment times, ensuring equitable timely and appropriate access;
-Ensure that patients are seen and treated in a safe environment, most appropriate to their care needs;
-Provide best value for money, delivering effective and sustainable use of resources.

This request covers the discovery stage of the public portal for the Defra Noise Modelling System being delivered under the NMS Framework agreement.  Specifically
-	Identification of users:
o	Categorised into user groups;
o	Definition of desired user journeys
o	Understanding current user journeys
-	Understand the problem to be solved, including:
o	Identifying any constraints associated with making changers to the service, e.g. technology or legislation;
o	Understanding the underlying policy intent to be addressed;
-	Identify opportunities for improvement
-	Inform design of user interface functionality and accessibility for various user groups

